<section id="manifesto" aria-labelledby="manifesto-heading">
	<div class="section-label">Policy Demands</div>
	<h2 id="manifesto-heading" class="manifesto-title">A Policy<br />Programme</h2>
	<p class="manifesto-intro">
		Thirty years of constitutional democracy have not reversed the
		inequality built over three centuries of colonial and apartheid
		extraction. These demands are not untested — each has historical
		precedent, existing legislative frameworks, and democratic mandate.
		They form the outline of a programme grounded in South Africa's
		specific crisis: a crisis of land, labour, capital, and ecological
		survival.
	</p>
	<div class="demands">
		<div class="demand reveal">
			<div class="demand-num" aria-hidden="true">01</div>
			<h3 class="demand-text">Land Restitution and Redistribution</h3>
			<div class="demand-sub">Enforce the Expropriation Act; implement Section 25 of the Constitution to expropriate land for redistribution without compensation where just and equitable; return productive agricultural land to dispossessed communities; end the concentration of commercial farmland in the hands of fewer than 40,000 white-owned farms</div>
		</div>
		<div class="demand reveal">
			<div class="demand-num" aria-hidden="true">02</div>
			<h3 class="demand-text">Implement National Health Insurance</h3>
			<div class="demand-sub">Fund NHI from a wealth levy and mining royalties; dismantle the two-tier private/public healthcare system; guarantee healthcare as a constitutional right rather than a commodity; end the market power of medical aid schemes and private hospital groups over health policy</div>
		</div>
		<div class="demand reveal">
			<div class="demand-num" aria-hidden="true">03</div>
			<h3 class="demand-text">Basic Income Guarantee</h3>
			<div class="demand-sub">Make permanent and expand the Social Relief of Distress grant as a full Basic Income Guarantee indexed to the food poverty line; fund from a progressive wealth tax and resource rents; extend to all adults regardless of employment status — ending the punishment of the unemployed for the failures of the economy</div>
		</div>
		<div class="demand reveal">
			<div class="demand-num" aria-hidden="true">04</div>
			<h3 class="demand-text">Democratic Control of Eskom and Mining</h3>
			<div class="demand-sub">Public ownership with democratic community governance; accelerated just transition out of coal with job and income guarantees for affected workers; end captive coal contracts; redirect mining royalties to affected communities; no privatisation of Eskom's generation or transmission assets to private capital</div>
		</div>
		<div class="demand reveal">
			<div class="demand-num" aria-hidden="true">05</div>
			<h3 class="demand-text">End Illicit Financial Flows</h3>
			<div class="demand-sub">Strengthen SARS enforcement capacity and resourcing; renegotiate the Mauritius double-taxation agreement to close profit-shifting loopholes; establish mandatory automatic information exchange with all offshore financial centres; create a public beneficial ownership register for all SA-registered companies and trusts</div>
		</div>
		<div class="demand reveal">
			<div class="demand-num" aria-hidden="true">06</div>
			<h3 class="demand-text">Restore Labour Rights</h3>
			<div class="demand-sub">Abolish the labour broker system; strengthen sectoral bargaining councils; enforce a living wage indexed to productivity; independent and resourced workplace health and safety inspectorate — Marikana cannot be the template for post-apartheid labour relations</div>
		</div>
		<div class="demand reveal">
			<div class="demand-num" aria-hidden="true">07</div>
			<h3 class="demand-text">Progressive Wealth and Inheritance Taxation</h3>
			<div class="demand-sub">Annual wealth tax on net assets above R50 million; inheritance levy above R10 million; compulsory acquisition of land above a democratically set productive ceiling; close the estate-duty loopholes used by trusts and family holding structures that perpetuate colonial-era wealth concentration across generations</div>
		</div>
		<div class="demand demand-full reveal">
			<div class="demand-num" aria-hidden="true">08</div>
			<h3 class="demand-text">Reparations and Restitution Fund</h3>
			<div class="demand-sub">A democratically governed national fund, resourced from mining royalties and wealth taxation, to compensate communities dispossessed under apartheid and colonialism — through land restitution, community infrastructure, pension top-ups, and educational grants. The wealth that built South Africa was built on stolen labour and stolen land. Its return is not generosity. It is justice.</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
